# School of Fish

**This page is a [redirect](/Wikipedia:Redirect).** For the actual phenomenon, see [Shoal](/Shoal). Because apparently we need to specify that "school of fish" doesn't mean Harvard for trout.

---

## Redirect Details

The following [categories](/Wikipedia:Categorizing_redirects) are applied to this page because we love bureaucracy:

• **[From an alternative name](/Category:Redirects_from_alternative_names)** – This is a redirect from a title that is another name or identity such as an alter ego, a nickname, or a synonym of the target, or of a name associated with the target. Because "school of fish" wasn't confusing enough already. Yes, let's pretend this is *merely* an alternative name rather than the term 99% of actual humans use. How delightfully academic.

• This redirect leads to the title in accordance with the naming conventions for [common names](/Wikipedia:Common_names) to aid searches and writing. Translation: we've decided to inconvenience you for your own good. You're welcome. It is [not necessary](/Wikipedia:NOTBROKEN) to replace these redirected links with a [piped link](/Wikipedia:Piped_link). Someone actually had to write that down. The tragedy.

• If this redirect is an incorrect name for the target, then {{[R from incorrect name](/Template:R_from_incorrect_name)}} should be used instead. Because what this situation desperately needs is more templates. Obviously.

